An interesting comment on the difference in feeling toward repetition between Homer and Quintus may be drawn from the statistics of Schmidt² and the observation of Paschal.³ Schmidt finds that there are 1804 verses in Homer, which together recur 4730 times, and that if slight differences be overlooked there are 2118 verses which appear together 5612 times. In striking contrast to this abundancc is the poverty of Quintus, from whose Posthomerica Paschal has gathered together a scanty collection cf five verses which recur every one once.
